        <wsdl:operation name="ActiveIssuesList" parameterOrder="Username Password Settings">
            <wsdl:documentation>
                Retrieves a list of all active issues and related information associated with the specified Site,
                Customer, SO, or the entire system.
                @param username A valid N-able N-central username
                @param password The password corresponding to the N-able N-central username
                @param settings A list of settings stored in an array of {@link T_KeyPair} objects. Below is a list of
                the acceptable Keys and Values.
                &lt;ul&gt;
                &lt;li&gt;Mandatory - (Key) customerid - (Value) The ID of the Site, Customer, or SO for which to
                retrieve active issues for. Use 1 to retrieve issues for all SOs and customers/sites.&lt;/li&gt;
                &lt;li&gt;(Key) searchBy - (Value) A value to search the so, site, device, deviceClass, service,
                transitionTime, notification, features, deviceID, and ip address.&lt;/li&gt;
                &lt;li&gt;(Key) orderby - (Value) The column of the Active Issues table to order the results by. Valid
                inputs are: customername, devicename, servicename, status, transitiontime,
                numberofacknoledgednotification, serviceorganization, deviceclass, licensemode, and endpointsecurity.
                Default is customername.&lt;/li&gt;
                &lt;li&gt;(Key) reverseorder - (Value) Determines whether the issues are returned in reverse order or
                not. Must be true or false. Default is false.&lt;/li&gt;
                &lt;/ul&gt;
                &lt;br/&gt;
                Filters can also be applied in the settings variable by following the table below. Multiple filters can
                be applied by adding more {@link T_KeyPair}s to the settings variable.
                &lt;p&gt;
                &lt;table&gt;
                &lt;thead&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;th&gt;Filter Type (Key)&lt;/th&gt;&lt;th&gt;Filter (Value)&lt;/th&gt;&lt;th&gt;Description&lt;/th&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/thead&gt;
                &lt;tbody&gt;
                &lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;NOC_View_Notification_Acknowledgement_Filter&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;"Acknowledged" or
                "Unacknowledged"&lt;/td&gt;
                &lt;td&gt;Filters by the notification status of the active issue&lt;/td&gt;
                &lt;/tr&gt;
                &lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;NOC_View_Status_Filter&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;no data&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Filters by
                "No Data" Status&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
                &lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;NOC_View_Status_Filter&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;stale&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Filters by
                "Stale" Status&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
                &lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;NOC_View_Status_Filter&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;normal&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Filters by
                "Normal" Status&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
                &lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;NOC_View_Status_Filter&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;warning&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Filters by
                "Warning" Status&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
                &lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;NOC_View_Status_Filter&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;failed&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Filters by
                "Failed" Status&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
                &lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;NOC_View_Status_Filter&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;misconfigured&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Filters
                by "Misconfigured" Status&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
                &lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;NOC_View_Status_Filter&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;disconnected&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;Filters
                by "Disconnected" Status&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
                &lt;/tbody&gt;
                &lt;/table&gt;
                &lt;/p&gt;
                @return An array of {@link DeviceIssue} objects, each representing one issue. Each {@link DeviceIssue}
                object contains an array of {@link T_KeyPair} which contain a key ({@link String}) and
                a value ({@link String}). Each {@link T_KeyPair} contains one piece of information about the issue.
                &lt;p&gt;
                &lt;table&gt;
                &lt;caption&gt;The following is a list of the keys used&lt;/caption&gt;
                &lt;tbody&gt;
                &lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;activeissue.sitename&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
                &lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;activeissue.customername&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;activeissue.customerid&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
                &lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;activeissue.socustomername&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;activeissue.socustomerid&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
                &lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;activeissue.deviceid&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;activeissue.devicename&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
                &lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;activeissue.deviceclass&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;activeissue.licensemode&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
                &lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;activeissue.isremotecontrollable&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;activeissue.notifstate&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
                &lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;activeissue.servicename&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;activeissue.serviceid&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
                &lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;activeissue.taskid&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;activeissue.taskident&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
                &lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;activeissue.transitiontime&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;activeissue.ispartofnotification&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
                &lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;activeissue.numberofactivenotification&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;activeissue.numberofacknowledgednotification&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
                &lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;activeissue.serviceitemid&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
                &lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;activeissue.isremotecontrolconnected&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;activeissue.psaintegrationexists&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
                &lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;activeissue.psaticketdetails&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
                &lt;/tbody&gt;
                &lt;/table&gt;
                &lt;/p&gt;
                @throws RemoteException if there are issues retrieving data from the database.
                &lt;p&gt;
                org.apache.axis.AxisFault
                &lt;ul&gt;
                &lt;li&gt;1012 - Thrown when mandatory settings are not present in "settings".&lt;/li&gt;
                &lt;li&gt;2100 - Thrown when invalid N-able N-central credentials are input.&lt;/li&gt;
                &lt;li&gt;5000 - An unexpected exception occurred.&lt;/li&gt;
                &lt;/ul&gt;
            </wsdl:documentation>
            <wsdl:input name="ActiveIssuesListRequest" message="impl:ActiveIssuesListRequest"/>
            <wsdl:output name="ActiveIssuesListResponse" message="impl:ActiveIssuesListResponse"/>
        </wsdl:operation>

        <wsdl:operation name="DevicePropertyList"
                        parameterOrder="Username Password DeviceIDs DeviceNames FilterIDs FilterNames ReverseOrder">
            <wsdl:documentation>
                Retrieves a list of the custom device properties for a list of devices.
                @param username the valid N-able N-central username.
                @param password the password corresponding to the N-able N-central username.
                @param deviceIDs the array of device IDs to filter the returned properties.
                @param deviceNames the array of device names to filter the returned properties.
                @param filterIDs the array of filter IDs to filter the returned properties.
                @param filterNames the array of filter Names to filter the returned properties.
                @param reverseOrder {@code false} for alphabetical order, or {@code true} for reverse alphabetical
                order.
                @return An array of {@link DeviceProperties} objects, containing the device's device name, device ID,
                URL, and an array of {@link DeviceProperty} objects containing device property label, value, device
                property ID, default value, and type.
                @throws RemoteException if there are issues retrieving data from the database.
                &lt;p&gt;
                org.apache.axis.AxisFault
                &lt;ul&gt;
                &lt;li&gt;2100 - Thrown when invalid N-able N-central credentials are input.&lt;/li&gt;
                &lt;li&gt;5000 - An unexpected exception occurred.&lt;/li&gt;
                &lt;/ul&gt;
            </wsdl:documentation>
            <wsdl:input name="DevicePropertyListRequest" message="impl:DevicePropertyListRequest"/>
            <wsdl:output name="DevicePropertyListResponse" message="impl:DevicePropertyListResponse"/>
        </wsdl:operation>

        <wsdl:operation name="DevicePropertyModify" parameterOrder="Username Password DeviceProperties">
            <wsdl:documentation>
                Modifies the custom device properties.
                @param username the valid N-able N-central username.
                @param password the password corresponding to the N-able N-central username.
                @param deviceProperties the device properties that you wish to populate. Only {@code deviceID} and
                {@code properties} are required in the DeviceProperties. In the {@code properties} only {@code devicePropertyID}
                 and {@code value} are used.
                @throws RemoteException if there are issues retrieving data from the database.
            </wsdl:documentation>
            <wsdl:input name="DevicePropertyModifyRequest" message="impl:DevicePropertyModifyRequest"/>
            <wsdl:output name="DevicePropertyModifyResponse" message="impl:DevicePropertyModifyResponse"/>
        </wsdl:operation>
        <wsdl:operation name="PSACredentialsValidate" parameterOrder="Version Username Password">
            <wsdl:documentation>
                Verifies whether the username and password are valid for a PSA interaction configuration.
                @param version Determines which type of PSA settings are being used Number which determines which type
                of PSA settings are being used
                &lt;ul&gt;
                &lt;li&gt;"1.0" indicates that a ConnectWise PSA integration is to be used.&lt;/li&gt;
                &lt;li&gt;"2.0" indicates that an Autotask PSA integration is to be used.&lt;/li&gt;
                &lt;li&gt;"3.0" indicates than a Tigerpaw PSA integration is to be used.&lt;/li&gt;
                &lt;/ul&gt;
                @param username the user-defined username for custom PSA settings.
                @param password the user-defined password for custom PSA settings.
                @return A boolean value stating whether or not the provided credentials are valid.
                @throws RemoteException if data cannot be retrieved properly from the database.
                &lt;p&gt;
                org.apache.axis.AxisFault
                &lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;5000 - An unexpected exception occurred.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;
            </wsdl:documentation>
            <wsdl:input name="PSACredentialsValidateRequest" message="impl:PSACredentialsValidateRequest"/>
            <wsdl:output name="PSACredentialsValidateResponse" message="impl:PSACredentialsValidateResponse"/>
        </wsdl:operation>


        <wsdl:operation name="CustomerList" parameterOrder="Username Password Settings">
            <wsdl:documentation>
                Retrieves a list of customers that belong to the service organization associated to the username given
                in the method parameters.
                @param username the N-able N-central username.
                @param password the corresponding N-able N-central password.
                @param settings A list of non default settings stored in an array of {@link T_KeyPair} objects. Below is
                a list of the acceptable Keys and Values. If not used leave {@code null}.
                &lt;ul&gt;
                &lt;li&gt;(Key) listSOs - (Value) "true" or "false". If true only SOs with be shown, if false only
                customers and sites will be shown. Default value is false.&lt;/li&gt;
                &lt;/ul&gt;
                @return An array of {@link Customer} objects, each representing one customer or site.
                Each {@link Customer} object contains an array of {@link T_KeyPair} which contain
                a key ({@link String}) and a value({@link String}).
                Each {@link T_KeyPair} contains one piece of information about the customer.
                &lt;p&gt;
                &lt;table&gt;
                &lt;caption&gt;The following is a list of the keys used&lt;/caption&gt;
                &lt;tbody&gt;
                &lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;customer.customerid&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;customer.customername&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
                &lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;customer.street1&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;customer.street2&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
                &lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;customer.city&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;customer.stateprov&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
                &lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;customer.postalcode&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;customer.county&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
                &lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;customer.phone&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;customer.contactfirstname&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
                &lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;customer.contactlastname&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;customer.contacttitle&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
                &lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;customer.contactdepartment&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;customer.contactphonenumber&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
                &lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;customer.contactext&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;customer.contactemail&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
                &lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;customer.issystem&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;customer.isserviceorg&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
                &lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;customer.parentid&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;customer.parentcustomername&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
                &lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;customer.externalid&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;customer.programlevelid&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
                &lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;customer.maintenancewindowstart&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td&gt;customer.maintenancewindowduration&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;
