        <wsdl:operation name="LastExportReset" parameterOrder="Version Username Password">
            <wsdl:documentation>
                The {@link #deviceAssetInfoExport(String, String, String)} method works incrementally. The first time it
                is called, it exports all applicable devices and then stores a "high-water mark" timestamp for when the
                call was made. The next time it is called, it only exports the incremental changes made since the
                last call: devices that have been modified, added, or deleted during that time span. Each time the
                API is called, another "high-water mark" timestamp is stored, and all are retained. When this method
                is called, it deletes the most recent "high-water mark" timestamp.
                &lt;p&gt;
                &lt;b&gt;Note:&lt;/b&gt; This does not repeat the last result set as it will move the "water mark" back
                to the one configured before the previous one and will return the result set from that one to the
                present.
                &lt;/p&gt;
                &lt;p&gt;
                &lt;img src='/dms/highwatermark.png'&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
                To use the illustration above as an example,
                if the {@link #deviceAssetInfoExport(String, String, String)} method is called at time T3, the result
                set R3 would only contain information that had not been previously returned at time T2 (the "high
                water mark" at the previous time that the call was made). If at time T3, this method was called, it
                would move the "high water mark" back to T1 and the result set would be the sum of R2 and R3 the next
                time that the {@link #deviceAssetInfoExport(String, String, String)} method is called.
                &lt;/p&gt;
                @param version Not used. Any non-null input is valid.
                @param username The user-defined username for custom PSA settings.
                @param password The user-defined password for custom PSA settings.
                @throws RemoteException if there is an error retrieving data from the database.
                &lt;p&gt;
                org.apache.axis.AxisFault
                &lt;ul&gt;
                &lt;li&gt;2001 - Required parameter is null - Thrown when null values are entered as inputs.&lt;/li&gt;
                &lt;li&gt;2001 - Thrown when a bad username-password combination is input, or no PSA integration has
                been set up.&lt;/li&gt;
                &lt;li&gt;5000 - An unexpected exception occurred.&lt;/li&gt;
                &lt;/ul&gt;
                @see #lastExportHardReset(String, String, String)
            </wsdl:documentation>
            <wsdl:input name="LastExportResetRequest" message="impl:LastExportResetRequest"/>
            <wsdl:output name="LastExportResetResponse" message="impl:LastExportResetResponse"/>
        </wsdl:operation>

        <wsdl:operation name="LastExportHardReset" parameterOrder="Version Username Password">
            <wsdl:documentation>
                Resets the "high-water mark" referenced in the {@link #deviceAssetInfoExport(String, String, String)}
                and {@link #deviceAssetInfoExport2(String, String, String)} APIs to its initial setting.
                @param version Not used. Any non-null input is valid.
                @param username The user-defined username for custom PSA settings.
                @param password The user-defined password for custom PSA settings.
                @throws RemoteException if there is an error retrieving data from the database.
                &lt;p&gt;
                org.apache.axis.AxisFault
